commit.message:
Made servos close more

They weren't closing enough

Works with user specified pattern now

The user can specify a pattern in the config.ini file and the program
will react to said pattern.

Now toggles servos on serial reading

Once it gets input from python it toggles the opening/closing of servos.

Added minimum threshold for clenching

This gets rid of the weird bug where a single clench would sometimes
double count

Create README.md

Moving onto hardware creation.

Fixed serial write to be an iterable

Supposed to be iterable not int, also added a timethreshold for easy
editing.

Arduino sketch reacts to serial input

LED blinks once detected input from python.
Consistent serial writing for double clench

Server serial integration

Server should now send a serial value of 1 if it should grip/ungrip.
Hopefully!

Create server.py

Creating our muse server
